{
  "abstract": "Crop productivity in the rainfed semi arid tropics (SAT) of India is low due to water shortage and\r\npoor fertility status of the soils. Earlier research have shown that SAT soils are critically deficient in\r\nZn, B and S in addition to N and P (Sahrawat et al., 2008; Wani et. al. 2009). For a sustainable\r\nincrease in productivity and enhancing the resilience in rainfed systems, the issues related to soil\r\nfertility needs to be addressed. The objective of this communication is to show as to how balanced\r\nnutrition involving Zn, B and S can be used to enhance crop productivity on sustainable basis in the\r\nsemi‐arid regions of India....",
